{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_adamsmorgan_ver01/data/sn84026749/0022225467A/1930010901/0186.xml":{"full_text":"STOCK MARKET\nRECOVERY\nIS SEEN\nThe era of caution has struck\naU markets throughout the coun\ntry, it was gathered today from\nopinions expressed by prominent\nbankers and financiers here.\n\u201cWild-cat speculation, which\nreached its peak last year, is now\na thing of the past.\u201d one of\nthese men declared. He pointed\nout that the public has learned\na lesson from the manner in\nwhich stock values crashed last\nOctober and November. Now.\naccording to his theory, the gen\neral public is investing and not\nspeculating.\nEra of Rebuilding\nThe bankers see as the imme\ndiate result of this investment\u2019\nstabilization of certain branches\nof business struck by the market\ncrash and also in a general era\nof rebuilding which will bring\nabout a permanent stability in\nthe stock market.\nMore than paper profits were\nwiped out during the market\ncrash, but this will all be re\nplaced in the new period of pros\nperity, it was pointed out.\nExperts on economics and fi\nnance declare the market is now\nentering into that period of up\nbuilding which always follows a\nsevere slump.\nPointing to the history of the\nstock markets they show that for\nseveral years the market will\nslowly rise; then will come a\nrapid increase in values, and\nwhen the very peak has been\nreached a slipping which in some\ninstances may reach panic pro\nportions.\nRehabilitation Begun\nNow, experts declare, the mar\nket is entering that after-slump\nrehabilitation and it may take\nmonths to start the steady rise,\nbut they are confident that it will\nbegin this year.\nThey do not anticipate, how\never, any decided gain in values\nsuch as were seen in 1929, but\nlook for steady increase.\nWith cities and States falling\nin behind the Hoover Administra\ntion\u2019s policy of stabilizing busi\nness, experts declare this will be\none of the factors that will speed\nup the period of rehabilitation\nwhich commerce, stocks and other\nvital parts of the country\u2019s in\nterest are now undergoing.\nNew- Metal Developed\nTo Go Into Radio Tubes\nNEW YORK, Jan. 9.\u2014Engineers\nV>f the Westinghouse Electric and\nManufacturing Company have de\nveloped, after many years of re\nsearch, a new metal which is said\nto be harder to forge than steel\nand to be exceedingly tough at\nvery high temperatures.\nThe new metal is called konel.\nIt can be used extensively in the\nmoving parts of internal combus\ntion engines and other extremely\nhot places, according to Westing\nhouse engineers.\nExtensive tests have revealed\nthat although most metals grow\nsofter and lose tensile strength as\nthey undergo high heat, konel\nheated to as high as 1,100 degrees\nFahrenheit will withstand a pres\nsure of 60,000 pounds to the square\ninch.\nOIL STOCKS~\n(Furnished by W, B. Hibba Jk Co.)\n(Bid j At*\nAnglo-American Oil (New).. 17 17%\nBorne-Scrymser Co 24 29\nBuckeye Pipe Line 69 70\nChesborough Mfg. Col6o 170\nContinental Oil Co 13%' 15%\nCumberland Pipe Line Co.. 40 43\nEureka Pipe Line 4S so\nGalena-Signal Oil, C0m.... 3 5\nHumble OU 83 85\nIllinois Pipe Line 302 308\nImperial OU of Canada....| 26 27\nIndiana Pipe Line 39 40\nInternational Pete 20% 21%\nNational Transit Co 21 22\nN. Y. Transportations C 0... 15 15%\nNorthern Pipe Line C0....|-50 53\nOhio Oil Co 70 71\nPenn Mexican Fuel 20 25\nSolar Refining Co 30 35\nSouthern Pipe Line Co 13 14%\nSouth Penn OU CoI 40%l 41\nSouthwestern Pipe Line Co.. I 57 63\nStandard Oil Co of Ind..! 53%i 54\nStandard OU Co of Kansas. 28 i 29%\nStandard OU Co Kentucky.! 33 34\nStandard OU Co of Nebraska! 43%I 45\nStandard OU-Co of 0hi0.... 85 I 88\nStandard OU Co of Ohio Pfd. 117% 1120\nSwan A Finch Co 6% 9\nVacuum OU Co 95 95%\nCHICAGO FUTURES\nGrains closed higher today.\nWheat was up %c to l%c; com,\n%c to %c; oats, %c to Voc.\nWheat started higher.\nA dip followed later, but offer\nings were well taken by commis\nsion houses and shorts. The buy\ning movement was Inspired by\nstrength in foreign markets and\nreports of sleet storms over our\nSouthwest. At $1.32 for May,\ntiiere was a mixed trade, but\nvolume of business was light and\nthe market easily influenced.\nLiverpool was up 1%@1%d, with\nshort covering and small offers\nof wheat from Russia.\nBuenos Aires was y 2 c higher.\nArgentine offers of wheat were\nlower early.\nCom covered a harrow range\nwith a limited trade. Country\nsales to arrive continued light.\nWeather conditions over the belt\nwere unsettled.\nEstimated carlot receipts were\nwheat, 10; com, 140, and oats, 28.\n(Furnished by W, B. Hibbs a Co.)\nlOpen High Low ICloae\nWheat\u2014 I\nMarch 128% 129% 128% 128%\nMay 183 133 131% 132%\nJ<ly :132% 188% 183 133\nJanuary 123%\nCorn\nMarch 30% 91% 90% 91%\nMay 84% 94% 84 94%\nJuly 95%| 96% 95% 96%\nOats\u2014 I\nMarch 47%| 47% 47%l 47%\nMay 49 I 49 48%l 48%\nJulv 47%| 47% 47%l 47%\nRye\u2014 I I j J\nMarch 1103 110 4 1103 1108\ntty 1109U1102 I100%!101%\nly ....\u2014......1109 UH%i 99 I 99\nRang* Sale*\u2014 Nat\n1939 Name Add High Low 11 :ll Ch'ge\nA\nS3H AWtiM PAP... 2 294 \u00a394\n27 25 Adams Exprwa.; 2 284 2f4 254+ 4\n23 22 Adv Rumlev pfd. 1 284 284 284\nH 4 Ahumada Lead... 1 H h 4\n1304 1224 Ah- Reduction,... 3 195 126 126 4- 4\n224 194 Airwav Bloc 1 22 22 22\n26 23 Allwrhanv C0r0... <5 244 244 214+ H\n265 255 HAI Chew Dva.... 1 258 2f\u00df 258\n\u2022'l4 494 Allis Chalmerg.. BM4 10 514+ 14\n214 20 Amerada 3 21 21 21 H\n86 4 77 Am Bank Noto 1 78 78 78\n94 8 Am Br Bo 88.... 2 94 94 94+ 4\n43H 41*4 Am Botch- 1 41 42 42\n474 47 Am Br Shoe 1 47 47 47\n12344 117 HAm Can 75 121 1204 122 4 14\n\u2022414 36*4 Am Chide.....*.. 4 404 394 -tO\n324 \u00a394 Am Con Ak0.... 5 3|H 304 314 4\n37 35 Am Eurott* Be.. 5 37 354 37 1\n994 89 Am Fo Pow l? 0 954 9>4 94)44 4\n108 107 Am F Ppf 1 1074 1074 1074- 4\n974 954 Am FA P 2nd pf 296 96 96\n214 194 Am Hawaii 88.. 1 214 ?14 -144 4\n394 374 Am 100 138 H 364\n874 86 Am Ice pfd 287 864 