ts.\n48c; firsts. In new cases, 45c; firsts, in\nsecond-hand cases. 44%c; seconds, 43\n044 c.\nCheese \u2014Sold I slowly at the inside\nrange of quotations: Whole-milk.\nhorps 2203i%c; single daisies, fresh.\nDULL MARKET\nFINDS TREND\nUPWARD\nBy W. 8. COUSINS\nNEW YORK, Jan. 9 (INJB.)x-\nIndustrial stocks were inclined\nmoderately upward in smother\ndull and unresponsive market this\nmorning. The bulls met with lit\ntle support in their efforts to mark\nup values on U. S. Steel, American\nCan and the specialties, though\nthey demonstrated their good in\ntentions by pushing big steel to\n170, for a 2-point gain; American\n123 y2 u 3 ld Dust,\nBethlehem and a few of the spe\ncialties a point or two Interna\ntional Nickel reached a new high\non the move to up iy 4 and\nmost of the utilities sold higher.\nThe stock market is now in a\nposition of waiting for something\nto turn up, and will probably re\nmain, in that position until signs\nof definite business revival appear\non the industrial horizon. Wall\nStreet believes that the first two\nor three months of 1930 will wipe\nout considerable of the uncer\ntainty now lingering in business\ncircles and pave the way for a bull\nmove in the stock market. Some\nimprovement was shown today in\nthe wobbly foreign exchange mar\nkets as well as in the market lor\noar silver.\nInvestment buying of the bet\nter grade of railroad stocks was\nseen in the moderate rallies in\nNew York Central, Pennsylvania,\nKaty, Baltimore and Ohio, South\nern Pacific, etc. The motors\nwe/e dull but firm, with General\nMotors up a point at 41 and\nStudebaker above 44. Gold Dust\nforged ahead 2 points to 41#\nwith the help ofthe new pool-or\npools, now industriously working\nin this stock.\nCommodity markets were firm\nin the early trading, with grain\nprices fractionally lower and cot\nton up 17 points.\nNEW YORK\nNEW YORK. Jan. 4.\u2014Live Stock\u2014Cat\ntle\u2014Market receipts, 130 head; directs,\n60 head. Supply largely cows of New\nYork ori